This program can be used to test a PWM DAC circuit. The ATmega168/328 should be
wired up as shown below:

                                 ATmega168/328
                                  +---\/---+
  +5V-------(PCINT14/RESET) PC6  1|        |28  PC5 (ADC5/SCL/PCINT13)
              (PCINT16/RXD) PD0  2|        |27  PC4 (ADC4/SDA/PCINT12)
              (PCINT17/TXD) PD1  3|        |26  PC3 (ADC3/PCINT11)------ROT0A
             (PCINT18/INT0) PD2  4|        |25  PC2 (ADC2/PCINT10)------ROT0B
        (PCINT19/OC2B/INT1) PD3  5|        |24  PC1 (ADC1/PCINT9)-------ROT1A
           (PCINT20/XCK/T0) PD4  6|        |23  PC0 (ADC0/PCINT8)-------ROT1B
           +5V--------------VCC  7|        |22  GND--------------GND
           GND--------------GND  8|        |21  AREF
 1-||--(PCINT6/XTAL1/TOSC1) PB6  9|        |20  AVCC-------------+5V
 6-||--(PCINT7/XTAL2/TOSC2) PB7 10|        |19  PB5 (SCK/PCINT5)
          (PCINT21/OC0B/T1) PD5 11|        |18  PB4 (MISO/PCINT4)
        (PCINT22/OC0A/AIN0) PD6 12|        |17  PB3 (MOSI/OC2A/PCINT3)
             (PCINT23/AIN1) PD7 13|        |16  PB2 (SS/OC1B/PCINT2)-----DAC1
         (PCINT0/CLKO/ICP1) PB0 14|        |15  PB1 (OC1A/PCINT1)--------DAC0
                                  +--------+

DAC:                 ____       ____
       5V PWM_in----|____|--+--|____|--+---DAC_out (0-5V)
                            |          |
                            =          =
                            |          |
                           GND        GND


Turning the rotary encoder changes the PWM duty cycle and hence the DAC output
voltage.
